<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4601778>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 1. — Englerodendron species:A-C, E.conchyliophorum (Pellegr.) Breteler;A, flower;B, flower longitudinal section;C, leaf axil with stipules; D-H, E. gabunense (J.Léonard) Breteler; D, flower; E, flower opened up; F, flower part showing, sepals,petals,stamens, and staminodes; G, H, leaf axil with enlargement; I-L, E. usambarense Harms; I, flower, some petals and some stamens missing; J, flower longitudinal section; K, L, leaf axil with enlargement. Abbreviations: a, axillary bud; s, stipule. A-C, Van Meer 1574; D, E, Breteler et al. 11081; F, Le Testu 7808; G, H, Breteler et al. 11174; I, J, Semsei 2942; K, L, Peter 48574. Drawing by H. de Vries. Scale bars: A, B, D-F, I, J, 1 cm; C, G, K, 3 cm; H, 5 mm, L, 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4601778/files/figure.png" .

